-- Lan Airlines Rises for Tenth Day in Chile After Disclosing Airbus Purchase
-- James Attwood
-- 2010-07-20T15:30:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/lan-airlines-rises-for-tenth-day-in-chile-after-disclosing-airbus-purchase.html

          
          
             Lan Airlines SA rose in Santiago
trading, heading for the longest winning streak in five years,
after agreeing to buy $4.2 billion in new aircraft.  
 Latin America’s biggest carrier by market value climbed 1.8
percent to a record 11,450 pesos at 11:19 a.m. New York time,
advancing for a tenth straight session.  
 Lan signed a memorandum of understanding to buy 50 A320
family planes from European Aeronautic Defence and Space
Company’s Airbus unit, the Santiago-based company wrote in an e-
mailed statement distributed today.  
          
          


  


        